37:35.213 --> 37:37.090
we don't have to worry about laundry.

37:37.090 --> 37:38.741
So I am happy.

37:39.884 --> 37:41.188
- There's more, let's go.

37:43.597 --> 37:44.806
All right, excited?
- Yes.

37:44.806 --> 37:46.193
- Come through.

37:46.193 --> 37:48.414
We have refreshed the menu, okay?

37:48.414 --> 37:50.207
- [Sandra] Oh my God.

37:50.207 --> 37:52.386
- Wow, breakfast pizza.
- I've worked with chef Brian

37:52.386 --> 37:55.369
to devise a short new menu that
will play to his strengths.

37:55.369 --> 37:57.266
First impressions visually.

37:57.266 --> 37:58.580
- It's very vibrant.

37:58.580 --> 38:00.134
- The presentation's amazing.

38:00.134 --> 38:03.429
- And the good news is two
thirds of the menu's gone.

38:03.429 --> 38:05.128
Chef, what'd you think?

38:05.128 --> 38:08.204
- I think that this allows
me to speak to the guest.

38:08.204 --> 38:11.301
- And Aaron, I want you as
a food and beverage manager,

38:11.301 --> 38:13.689
take responsibility of room service.

38:13.689 --> 38:16.671
Own it and no plastic containers.

38:16.671 --> 38:18.715
- I think now we have
the proper education,

38:18.715 --> 38:20.456
the proper understanding of the menu.

38:20.456 --> 38:21.676
With limited smaller items,

38:21.676 --> 38:23.313
we definitely can execute it a lot quicker

38:23.313 --> 38:24.971
and now I feel a lot more comfortable.

38:24.971 --> 38:27.964
- And that for me is great news

38:27.964 --> 38:29.517
'cause it means the
front desk is no longer

38:29.517 --> 38:31.280
looking after room
service or doing laundry.

38:31.280 --> 38:32.698
They can concentrate
- Thank you.

38:32.698 --> 38:34.671
- on looking after the guests.

38:34.671 --> 38:35.622
- Yes.

38:35.622 --> 38:37.977
- There's one more change we need to do.

38:38.943 --> 38:42.040
You've be wearing a red chef
jacket for far too long.

38:42.040 --> 38:45.273
You deserve a white one, let me tell you.

38:45.273 --> 38:47.660
Put that on, enjoy it.
- Thank you.

38:47.660 --> 38:49.068
- I certainly will.

38:49.068 --> 38:50.445
I'm feeling great.

38:50.445 --> 38:54.490
I'm no longer Eddie's
chef in the red jacket.

38:54.490 --> 38:59.328
I'm the chef of the Merk Bistro in white.

38:59.328 --> 39:00.653
- It's not Eddie's favourite colour,

39:00.653 --> 39:03.520
but it is a proper chef jacket.

39:03.520 --> 39:04.886
YOu perform like one,

39:04.886 --> 39:07.138
you deserve it, make it yours.

39:07.138 --> 39:08.726
- Thank you, Gordon.
- Well done.

39:09.933 --> 39:12.748
- This is the kind of energy
you wanna see every day.

39:12.748 --> 39:13.760
So you know what?

39:13.760 --> 39:15.209
As long as they're doing their jobs,

39:15.209 --> 39:17.951
I have no problem with them
saying no to me anymore.

39:17.951 --> 39:18.820
- Big night tonight.

39:18.820 --> 39:20.391
There's gonna be a packed restaurant.

39:20.391 --> 39:24.134
You've got to remember
you're all team Keating.

39:24.134 --> 39:25.003
I know you can do it.

39:25.003 --> 39:26.814
- [Sandra] Oh absolutely, absolutely.

39:27.894 --> 39:31.486
(dramatic music)

39:31.486 --> 39:32.354
- [Gordon] Guests are arriving

39:32.354 --> 39:34.207
for the relaunch of the Keating hotel

39:35.135 --> 39:37.813
and the first impressions
are very positive.

39:37.813 --> 39:39.172
- This is really nice.

39:39.172 --> 39:40.447
- You like it?
- Oh yeah.

39:40.447 --> 39:42.173
- Oh this is beautiful.
- Whao.

39:42.173 --> 39:44.572
- At long last, the front desk can focus

39:44.572 --> 39:45.781
on welcoming guests.

39:45.781 --> 39:46.650
- How are you?
- Nice to see you.

39:46.650 --> 39:49.104
- Welcome, I'm Cindy, pleasure to meet you

39:49.104 --> 39:50.828
- [Gordon] And the hotels new white lobby

39:50.828 --> 39:52.256
is a great improvement.

39:52.256 --> 39:53.125
- Wasn't this all red?

39:53.125 --> 39:54.519
and before it looked like a bus station,

39:54.519 --> 39:56.041
Now it looks like how
it looks like a hotel.

39:56.041 --> 39:58.367
It looks much more inviting.

39:58.367 --> 40:02.162
- [Gordon] At the restaurant,
Aaron is finally stepping up

40:02.162 --> 40:04.435
and taking a new hands on
approach to room service.

40:04.435 --> 40:05.304
Go on, go on, come on, quick.

40:05.304 --> 40:07.882
And not a plastic container in sight.

40:07.882 --> 40:10.796
(lively music)

40:10.796 --> 40:12.074
- Mr. Hanks, right?
- Yeah, hi.

40:12.074 --> 40:13.027
- Excellent, we've got room service

40:13.027 --> 40:14.831
over here for you.

40:14.831 --> 40:16.343
- [Gordon] The simplified menu has brought

40:16.343 --> 40:17.865
Brian back to life.

40:17.865 --> 40:21.139
- [Brian] I want the most
gorgeous plates in the world

40:21.139 --> 40:23.485
coming up in this window.

40:23.485 --> 40:24.872
- [Gordon] That's good
news for the diners.

40:24.872 --> 40:27.135
- So beautiful.
- It's very tender.

40:27.135 --> 40:28.855
It's like, I don't even need this knife.

40:28.855 --> 40:30.711
- This is a joint where
you don't need ketchup

40:30.711 --> 40:31.827
because it's perfectly seasoned.

40:31.827 --> 40:34.413
- And for the future of
Eddie and the Keating hotel.

40:34.413 --> 40:35.915
Keep it going.

40:35.915 --> 40:36.960
- That's amazing.

40:36.960 --> 40:40.430
- Look how tender that is.
- It's perfect.

40:40.430 --> 40:42.341
- If I had one thing to
say to Gordon right now,

40:42.341 --> 40:44.854
it's just thanks.

40:45.852 --> 40:49.428
All right, ladies and gentlemen,
it's our last ticket out.

40:49.428 --> 40:53.839
I've been really lost here
and you've woken me up.

40:53.839 --> 40:56.198
Great job, new day, new day.

40:57.342 --> 40:58.941
And reminded me of who I am.

41:06.101 --> 41:08.218
- This place was all about Eddie's dream

41:08.218 --> 41:10.731
of what a hotel should be like.

41:10.731 --> 41:14.477
But he forgot the most
important person, the guest.

41:15.517 --> 41:18.301
I'm just hoping that
Eddie can trust his staff

41:18.301 --> 41:20.042
and let them work as a team

41:20.042 --> 41:22.318
because this is a place
I'd love to come back to.

41:24.140 --> 41:27.435
Okay, right, Sandra,

41:27.435 --> 41:29.791
you are a great general manager.

41:29.791 --> 41:31.731
Don't stop being one, okay?

41:31.731 --> 41:33.690
- Gordon, thank you.

41:33.690 --> 41:35.084
Thank you so much, thank you so much.

41:35.084 --> 41:38.123
I'm proud to be the general
manager of the Keaton Hotel.

41:38.123 --> 41:39.085
- Give me a hug.

41:42.898 --> 41:44.035
Hey well done, seriously.

41:44.035 --> 41:45.223
You can do the food and beverage.

41:45.223 --> 41:47.747
You can handle the room service easily.

41:47.747 --> 41:50.927
And my God, I mean, you
bounce back from the dead

41:50.927 --> 41:52.016
let me tell you.
- Literally.

41:52.016 --> 41:53.471
- Literally.
- Yeah, literally.

41:53.471 --> 41:55.025
Make it yours, okay?
- Oh it is mine.

41:55.025 --> 41:59.050
- Well done and do not
change that jacket, okay?

41:59.050 --> 42:01.351
White suits you, you know that?

42:01.351 --> 42:04.712
And let your team run your business, okay?

42:04.712 --> 42:06.130
- I think this experience with Gordon

42:06.130 --> 42:08.153
was life-changing for everyone here.

42:08.153 --> 42:10.259
What you did to get
the team back together,

42:10.259 --> 42:12.227
I mean, I'm telling you,
no one could have done.

42:12.227 --> 42:15.139
- But this place is on
the road and good luck.

42:15.139 --> 42:16.411
I can't wait to come back.

42:16.411 --> 42:18.896
- It's one of those experiences
you'll never forget.

42:20.154 --> 42:21.023
- Good job, guys.

42:21.023 --> 42:22.290
- Sometimes you have to trust me.

42:22.290 --> 42:23.886
- No.
- No, no,

42:23.886 --> 42:24.755
no, no.

42:56.370 --> 42:59.151
- [Girl] One potato, two potato.
